RADULA (n = 3). Comprises 110–114 transverse rows with 69–77 teeth per row; radular formula: (22–24)- (12–14)-1-(12–14)-(22–24). Central and lateral teeth unicuspid, tongue-shaped. Central tooth smaller and shorter than lateral teeth (
Fig. 6M–N
). Marginal teeth asymmetric, tricuspid with small endocone; mesocone large with curved margins; ectocone triangular and located at tooth base (
Fig. 6N–O
).
